          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An irradiation head with three targets in",
                "series was used, which allowed the simultaneous",
                "irradiation of two actinide samples and an 27Al monitor",
                "rodlet, the targets themselves not affecting the proton",
                "beam significantly."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  High-fluence irradiations make it",
                "possible to produce enough fission and spallation",
                "products to use inductively coupled plasma mass",
                "spectrometry as the analytical technique.  This method",
                "is the best for the measurement of isobaric production",
                "cross sections, since the cumulative isobaric mass",
                "yields in the beta-decay range, mass numbers <204, do",
                "not depend on time."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the correction of matrix effects, a known amount of",
                "a thulium standard was added as an internal standard to",
                "all sample solutions.  169-Tm was selected as indicator",
                "isotope since there was no detectable signal on mass",
                "169 in the concentrated solutions of both actinide",
                "targets.   Thus, the possibility of interfering effects",
                "with any fission product in this mass range could be",
                "excluded.",
                "Certain volatile and/or insoluble irradiation  products",
                "could not contribute to the measured mass yields and",
                "thus rendered the corresponding isobaric production",
                "cross sections too low.  This was particularly the case",
                "for several isotopes of the noble gases krypton and",
                "xenon, as well as for the insoluble oxides of palladium",
                "and tin.  The corresponding mass yields were upscaled",
                "by using calculated extrapolation factors, deduced by",
                "following a procedure similar to that used for  results",
                "from gamma-spectrometry.  The correction factor values",
                "were mostly in the range 1 to 3.  For mass numbers 106,",
                "108, and 110, the insoluble oxides of palladium have",
                "dominant contributions, and the corresponding",
                "correction factors were between 3 and 6."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
